  <h2>üìÑ Project Proposal</h2>
  <h3>Designing Workflow Models for Medical Device Failure Reporting ‚Äì Digital Twin</h3>

  <h3>üéØ Objective</h3>
  <p>
    Pacemakers are Class III life-sustaining medical devices. Traditional check-ups can miss early signs of failure like battery drainage or lead fracture. Our project proposes integrating Digital Twin (DT) technology for real-time monitoring, predictive failure detection, and instant alerts.
  </p>
  <p>
    A Digital Twin is a virtual replica of a physical system. Combined with IoT sensors and AI, it enables continuous data monitoring, anomaly detection, and automated alerts, transforming patient safety and medical responsiveness.
  </p>

  <h3>üõ†Ô∏è Proposed Design Approach</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>IoT Sensors:</strong> Collect data like heart rate, voltage, and battery life.</li>
    <li><strong>Wireless Transmission:</strong> Data sent via Wi-Fi/Bluetooth to a cloud-based DT.</li>
    <li><strong>Digital Twin System:</strong> Simulates pacemaker behavior using:
      <ul>
        <li>Manufacturer specifications</li>
        <li>Patient-specific patterns</li>
        <li>AI learning from past data</li>
      </ul>
    </li>
    <li><strong>AI Anomaly Detection:</strong> Categorizes risks and sends alerts to experts instantly.</li>
  </ul>

  <p><strong>System Diagrams (in progress):</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Data Flow from Pacemaker to DT</li>
    <li>AI Failure Detection Logic</li>
    <li>Alert System Workflow</li>
  </ul>

  <table>
    <tr>
      <th>Feature</th>
      <th>Traditional Monitoring</th>
      <th>Proposed DT System</th>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>Data Collection</td>
      <td>Periodic checkups</td>
      <td>Real-time continuous data</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>Failure Detection</td>
      <td>Post-failure</td>
      <td>Predictive AI alerts</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>Response Time</td>
      <td>Delayed</td>
      <td>Instant notification</td>
    </tr>
  </table>

  <h3>‚öôÔ∏è Realistic Constraints</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Regulations:</strong> ISO 14708-1, ISO 13485, HIPAA</li>
    <li><strong>Cybersecurity:</strong> Encrypted data, no remote tampering</li>
    <li><strong>Power Efficiency:</strong> Sensor design must preserve pacemaker battery</li>
    <li><strong>Cost:</strong> AI: $50K‚Äì$500K, IoT: $50K‚Äì$1M+</li>
    <li><strong>Environmental Impact:</strong> Minimizing e-waste, avoiding signal interference</li>
    <li><strong>Ethical Concerns:</strong> Data privacy, fairness, AI transparency</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>üìà Project Work Plan</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Literature Review & Research (WP1)</li>
    <li>Define IoT‚ÄìDT interaction (WP2)</li>
    <li>System Diagrams & Flowcharts (WP3)</li>
    <li>Compliance & Ethics Research (WP4)</li>
    <li>Prepare Final Report & Presentation (WP5)</li>
  </ul>

